VALUES
(42, 12, 38, 40, 25, 6, 6, NULL, 'Servants Awaiting the Bridegroom', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of vigilance and readiness for the coming of the master or bridegroom. The mention of specific times in Luke and the midnight cry in Matthew highlight the importance of being prepared at any hour.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 38, 52, 5, 4, 5, 'blessed are those servants', 'Servants and Children of Light', 'Both passages emphasize vigilance and readiness. Luke speaks of servants being blessed if found prepared, while 1 Thessalonians assures believers are not in darkness, highlighting their preparedness for the coming day.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 39, 61, 3, 10, 10, 'thief would come', 'Theft and Vigilance Theme', 'Both passages emphasize the unexpected nature of a thief''s arrival, highlighting the need for vigilance. Luke 12:39 warns of a thief coming to break in, while 2 Peter 3:10 describes the day of the Lord coming as a thief in the night.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 39, 66, 3, 3, 3, 'thief would come', 'Theft and Vigilance Theme', 'Both passages emphasize the need for vigilance against unexpected events, using the metaphor of a thief. The warning in Revelation echoes the idea in Luke that one must be prepared to avoid loss.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 39, 66, 16, 15, 15, 'if the goodman of the house had known', 'The Thief Motif in Scripture', 'This connection highlights the theme of vigilance against unexpected events. Both passages emphasize the need to be watchful, as the arrival of the thief symbolizes sudden and unforeseen occurrences.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 39, 40, 24, 43, 44, 'if the goodman of the house had known', 'Readiness for the Unexpected', 'Both passages emphasize the need for vigilance and readiness against unexpected events, using the metaphor of a thief coming to break into a house. This connection highlights the urgency of being prepared for the coming of the Son of man.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 39, 52, 5, 2, 3, 'if the goodman of the house had known', 'Theft and Vigilance Theme', 'This connection highlights the theme of unexpected arrival and the need for vigilance. Both passages emphasize the idea of being unprepared for an imminent event, likening it to a thief''s sudden intrusion.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 39, 40, 6, 19, 19, NULL, 'Connection of Thieves and Vigilance', 'Both passages emphasize the threat of thieves and the need for vigilance. Luke 12:39 warns of a thief coming unexpectedly, while Matthew 6:19 mentions thieves breaking through to steal treasures.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 40, 52, 5, 6, 6, 'Be ye therefore ready also', 'Readiness for Christ''s Return', 'Both passages emphasize the need for vigilance and readiness for the coming of the Son of Man. Luke 12:40 warns that He will come unexpectedly, while 1 Thessalonians 5:6 encourages believers to stay awake and alert.', 'theme', 0.46099999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 40, 40, 25, 13, 13, 'the Son of man cometh at an hour when ye think not', 'Readiness for the Son of Man', 'Both passages emphasize the need for vigilance and readiness for the coming of the Son of Man, highlighting the uncertainty of the timing. They stress that His arrival will occur unexpectedly, urging believers to be prepared at all times.', 'theme', 0.43299999999999994, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 40, 45, 13, 11, 11, 'Be ye therefore ready also', 'Readiness for Salvation', 'Both passages emphasize the urgency of being prepared for the coming of the Son of Man. Luke 12:40 warns that His arrival will be unexpected, while Romans 13:11 calls for awakening from sleep, indicating that salvation is imminent.', 'theme', 0.419, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 40, 40, 24, 44, 44, NULL, 'Readiness for the Son of Man', 'Both passages emphasize the need for readiness as the Son of Man will come unexpectedly. The phrasing about coming ''at an hour when ye think not'' is a direct parallel, underscoring the urgency of being prepared.', 'parallel', 0.412, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 40, 61, 3, 12, 14, 'Be ye therefore ready also', 'Readiness for Christ''s Return', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of being ready for the coming of the Lord. Luke 12:40 warns that the Son of man will come unexpectedly, while 2 Peter 3:14 encourages diligence to be found blameless at His coming.', 'theme', 0.412, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 40, 66, 19, 7, 7, 'Be ye therefore ready also', 'Readiness for the Coming', 'This connection highlights the theme of readiness in both passages. Luke emphasizes being prepared for the unexpected return of the Son of Man, while Revelation speaks of the bride making herself ready for the marriage of the Lamb.', 'theme', 0.40499999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 40, 41, 13, 33, 36, 'for the Son of man cometh', 'Readiness for the Son of Man', 'Both passages emphasize the need for vigilance and readiness for the coming of the Son of Man. They highlight the uncertainty of the timing of his return, urging believers to be prepared at all times.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 41, 41, 13, 37, 37, NULL, 'Call to Vigilance', 'This connection highlights the theme of vigilance in both passages. Peter''s inquiry in Luke about who the parable is directed to reflects a concern for readiness, which is echoed in Mark''s directive to ''Watch.''', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 41, 60, 4, 7, 7, NULL, 'Connection Between Readiness and Prayer', 'This connection highlights the theme of preparedness in both passages. Peter''s inquiry about the audience in Luke reflects a concern for readiness, which is echoed in 1 Peter''s call to be sober and watchful in prayer as the end approaches.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 41, 41, 14, 37, 37, NULL, 'Peter''s Vigilance and Sleep', 'This connection highlights Peter''s struggle with vigilance in both passages. In Luke, Peter''s question reflects concern about understanding Jesus'' teachings, while in Mark, his inability to stay awake signifies a failure to heed those teachings.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 41, 60, 5, 8, 8, NULL, 'Vigilance Against Adversaries', 'This connection highlights the theme of vigilance in both passages. In Luke, Peter''s inquiry reflects a concern for understanding the teachings about being prepared, while 1 Peter emphasizes the need for vigilance against the devil as an adversary.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 42, 40, 24, 45, 46, 'faithful and wise steward', 'Connection of Stewardship Themes', 'Both passages emphasize the role of a faithful and wise steward or servant appointed to manage a household. They highlight the expectation of providing for others in due season and the blessing for being found diligent in this task.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 42, 46, 4, 1, 2, 'faithful and wise steward', 'Stewardship and Faithfulness', 'Both passages emphasize the role of stewards and the requirement of faithfulness. Luke highlights the faithful steward''s responsibility, while 1 Corinthians stresses that stewards must be found faithful in their duties.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 42, 60, 5, 1, 4, 'faithful and wise steward', 'Stewardship and Leadership', 'This connection highlights the role of faithful stewardship in both passages. Luke emphasizes the wise steward''s responsibility to provide, while Peter calls elders to ''Feed the flock of God,'' linking the concepts of care and oversight.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 42, 58, 13, 17, 17, 'faithful and wise steward', 'Stewardship and Accountability', 'This connection highlights the theme of stewardship and accountability in both passages. Luke emphasizes the role of the faithful steward, while Hebrews calls for obedience to those who watch over souls, indicating a responsibility to care for others.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 42, 60, 4, 10, 10, 'faithful and wise steward', 'Stewardship and Service Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of stewardship in both passages. Luke 12:42 speaks of a faithful steward tasked with providing for others, while 1 Peter 4:10 emphasizes being good stewards of God''s grace by serving one another.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 42, 42, 19, 15, 19, 'faithful and wise steward', 'Faithful Stewardship and Reward', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of faithful stewardship and the rewards that come from it. In Luke 12:42, the faithful steward is entrusted with the household, while in Luke 19:15-19, the servants are rewarded for their faithfulness in trading the money given to them.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 42, 44, 20, 28, 28, NULL, 'Stewardship and Feeding the Flock', 'This connection highlights the theme of stewardship in both passages. Luke emphasizes the role of a faithful steward to provide for the household, while Acts calls overseers to feed the church, indicating a responsibility to care for others.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 44, 42, 22, 29, 30, 'ruler over all that he hath', 'Rulership and Kingdom Authority', 'This connection highlights the theme of rulership, as both passages discuss being appointed to positions of authority. In Luke 12:44, the faithful servant is promised rulership over all that he has, while in Luke 22:29-30, the disciples are appointed a kingdom to rule alongside Jesus.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 44, 40, 24, 47, 47, 'ruler over all that he hath', 'Rulership Over Goods Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of being made ruler over possessions. The similar phrasing in both verses highlights the reward of stewardship and responsibility over goods.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 44, 42, 19, 17, 19, 'ruler over all that he hath', 'Faithfulness and Authority', 'Both passages emphasize the reward of faithfulness with increased authority. In Luke 12:44, being made ''ruler over all that he hath'' parallels the granting of authority over cities in Luke 19:17-19.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 44, 27, 12, 2, 3, 'ruler over all that he hath', 'Rulership and Reward', 'This connection highlights the theme of reward for faithfulness. Both passages emphasize the idea of being made ruler or shining brightly as a result of wise actions.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
